Ted Mukuria (left) with other participants during a tree planting exercise in Mpeketoni earlier this week. Mukuria, a conservationist is the grandson of the late freedom fighter Dedan Kimathi died after a short illness. [File, Standard]  The family of Kenya’s freedom fighter Dedan Kimathi is mourning following the death of his grandson who was an environmental conservationist.  Ted Mukuria was the son of Evelyn Wanjugu, Kimathi's daughter. He died on Tuesday night at the Mpeketoni sub-County Hospital where he had been rushed to.  “My son developed complications and his roommates took him to hospital,” she said.  Wanjugu, the CEO of Dedan Kimathi Foundation said that her son was pronounced dead minutes after he arrived at the facility.   By Fred Kagonye | 1 hour ago By Joackim Bwana | 1 hour ago By Joackim Bwana | 3 hours ago By Kamore Maina and Brian Okoth | 4 hours ago